thumbright.label: Thumb Ranges of Motion Figures 16-12 page 456, 16-15 page 457, 16-16 page 458, 16-19 page 460: AMA Estimated Normal: IP Flexion (80D) IP Extension (+30D), MP Flexion (60D) MP Extension (+40D), Radial Abduction (50D), Adduction (0cm), Opposition (Measured as largest possible distance (cm) from IP flexor crease to distal palmar crease (see page 459) (8cm). Motion is measured with goniometer and is reported right over left side in Degrees (D) except adduction and opposition which are measured in centimeters (cm).
thumbright.textareatext: Hyper-extension is measured with a '+' preceeding the measurement. i.e. +10 = 10 degrees of hyper-extension.

thumbright.label: Actual goniometer measurements of the range of motion are only required for PR-4 (Permanent & Stationary) reports. Visual estimates of the range of motion may be adequate for Doctor's First reports and PR-2 reports.

options: Mild - Inconsistent triggering during active range of motion
